(1249, 3, '2016-07-31 23:05:30', '2016-08-01 03:05:30', 'À tort ou à raison, les gens semblent mettre sur le même pied Walmart store inc. et Costco Wholesale Corporation.\n\nVoici quelques chiffres qui vont être utiles ;\n\n<strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1250" src="http://localhost/brut44/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/image1-15-e1470017183609.jpg" alt="image1" width="400" height="123" /></strong>\n\nRevenues 117,9 Milliards\n\nProfits 15,13 Milliards\n\nProfits Net 2,35 Milliards\n\n/Valeur de la compagnie en bourse 73 milliards\n\n<strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1251" src="http://localhost/brut44/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/image2-17.jpg" alt="image2" width="240" height="76" /></strong>\n\nRevenues 483,2 Milliards\n\nProfits 121,1 Milliards\n\nProfits Net 14,5 Milliards\n\n/Valeur de la compagnie en bourse 227 Milliards\n\n<strong>Le point en commun entre les deux "Behemoths" du commerce au détail c''est bien sûr leurs clientèles Hétéroclites.</strong>\n\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1258" src="http://localhost/brut44/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/image1-16.jpg" alt="image1" width="236" height="314" />\n\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1257" src="http://localhost/brut44/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/image2-18-e1470019335903.jpg" alt="image2" width="500" height="660" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<img class="size-full wp-image-1256" src="http://localhost/brut44/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/image3-8.jpg" alt="JPEG Pro" width="640" height="359" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1255" src="http://localhost/brut44/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/image4-2.jpg" alt="image4" width="600" height="450" />\n\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1252" src="http://localhost/brut44/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/image9-e1470019471124.jpg" alt="image9" width="500" height="588" />\n\n<img class="size-full wp-image-1254" src="http://localhost/brut44/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/image6.jpg" alt="402065 04: Mary LaRocca offers a sample of Libby''s Vienna Sausage in a Costco Wholesale store March 8, 2002 in Niles, IL. Warehouse retailer Costco Wholesale Corp. has reported higher quarterly profits as the promise of bulk goods at bargain prices resonated with consumers in the U.S. recession. Warehouse retailers charge customers an annual membership fee, typically $35 to $45, to shop at clubs that offer deep discounts on bulk quantities of items like food and household cleaners. (Photo by Tim Boyle/Getty Images)" width="570" height="238" />\n\n&nbsp;', 'Les monstres et leurs clients', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'les-monstres-et-leurs-clients', '', '', '2016-07-31 23:05:30', '2016-08-01 03:05:30', '', 0, 'http://brut44.com/?p=1249', 0, 'post', '', 0),
